snippet.textDisplay: Thanks very much for a very interesting programme. I have a doubt, however, regarding the market in Wuhan. I accept what you say about the dangers of a growing demand for consumption of wild animals, but looking at the conditions of the market in Wuhan, I would doubt that the super-rich buy their food there. I would rather imagine that the clients of such a market would be the hangers-on and those who seek to emulate the super-rich, but in a much lower income bracket. I don't want to simply shift the blame, because these people don't pull the strings in the government, but I think an extra layer of complexity might be necessary.
